CCR4-NOT transcription complex subunit 3 (CNOT3) is up-regulated in lung cancer tissues and is associated with poor prognosis of the patients. Knocking down CNOT3 expression sensitizes cisplatin-resistant A549 (A549/DDP) cells to cisplatin-induced apoptosis. CNOT3 depletion up-regulates the expression level of RIPK3 and the enhanced apoptosis is mediated by the elevated RIPK3 to further trigger Caspase 8 activation.
